# üåø Paludarium Controller - WiFi Setup Manual

## Quick Start Guide

### What's in the Box
- ‚úÖ Paludarium Controller (ESP32-S3 based)
- ‚úÖ Power adapter
- ‚úÖ Sensor cables (DHT11, DS18B20, Water Level)
- ‚úÖ Relay connection cables
- ‚úÖ Quick start card

---

## üì± Initial WiFi Setup (First Time Only)

### Step 1: Power On Your Device
1. Connect the power adapter to your Paludarium Controller
2. Wait 30 seconds for the device to boot up
3. Look for the **blue LED** to indicate setup mode is active

### Step 2: Connect to Setup Network
1. On your phone/tablet, go to **WiFi Settings**
2. Look for the network named: **`Paludarium_Setup`**
3. Connect to this network using password: **`paludarium`**
4. Wait for connection confirmation

### Step 3: Open Setup Interface
1. Open your web browser (Safari, Chrome, Firefox, etc.)
2. Go to: **`192.168.4.1`**
3. You should see the "Paludarium WiFi Setup" page
4. If the page doesn't load, try: **`http://192.168.4.1`**

### Step 4: Scan for Your Network
1. Click the **"üîÑ Refresh Scan"** button
2. Wait for the list of available networks to appear
3. Find your home WiFi network in the list
4. Click on your network name to select it

### Step 5: Enter WiFi Password
1. Your network name will appear in the "Network Name" field
2. Enter your WiFi password in the "Password" field
3. **Important**: Password is case-sensitive!
4. Double-check spelling and capitalization

### Step 6: Save & Connect
1. Click **"üíæ Save & Connect"**
2. You'll see a confirmation message
3. The device will automatically restart (takes ~30 seconds)
4. The setup network will disappear

### Step 7: Find Your Device
1. Reconnect your phone to your home WiFi
2. Find your device's new IP address using one of these methods:
   - Check your router's admin page for "Paludarium" or "ESP32"
   - Use a network scanner app (Fing, WiFi Analyzer)
   - Check your router's DHCP client list

---

## üéõÔ∏è Using Your Paludarium Controller

### Accessing the Control Panel
1. Open your web browser
2. Go to your device's IP address (e.g., `192.168.1.100`)
3. Bookmark this page for easy access!

### Control Modes
- **ü§ñ AUTO Mode**: Follows natural schedule (rain at 8am/8pm, etc.)
- **üì± MANUAL Mode**: Full control via phone/tablet
- **üîí MANUAL LOCK**: Stays in manual mode until unlocked

### Quick Controls
- **Tap any button** to toggle devices on/off
- **Hold button 1.5 seconds** to toggle manual lock
- **Quick Actions**: Morning, Night, Mist Boost, Party Mode
- **Live Settings**: Adjust temperature, humidity, timing in real-time

---

## üîß Troubleshooting

### ‚ùå Can't Find "Paludarium_Setup" Network
**Solutions:**
- Wait 60 seconds after powering on
- Perform factory reset (see below)
- Make sure you're within 10 feet of the device
- Refresh your phone's WiFi list

### ‚ùå Setup Page Won't Load
**Solutions:**
- Try `http://192.168.4.1` (include "http://")
- Disable mobile data/cellular
- Try a different browser
- Restart your phone's WiFi

### ‚ùå "Connection Failed" After Entering Password
**Solutions:**
- Double-check WiFi password (case-sensitive!)
- Make sure network is 2.4GHz (not 5GHz only)
- Try moving device closer to router during setup
- Check if network has special characters in name/password

### ‚ùå Device Not Appearing on Home Network
**Solutions:**
- Wait 2-3 minutes for full connection
- Check router logs for new devices
- Restart your router
- Perform factory reset and try again

---

## üîÑ Factory Reset

### When to Factory Reset
- Moving to a new location/network
- WiFi password changed
- Can't connect to device
- Selling/giving away the device

### How to Factory Reset
1. **Power on** the device
2. **Access the control panel** (if possible)
3. **Hold any control button** for 10 seconds
4. **Alternative**: Turn any device on via manual control and leave it running for 10 seconds
5. Watch for confirmation in device logs
6. Device will restart in setup mode

---

## üìã Technical Specifications

### WiFi Requirements
- **Frequency**: 2.4GHz networks only
- **Security**: WPA/WPA2/WPA3 supported
- **Range**: Up to 50 meters from router
- **Password**: Up to 63 characters

### Browser Compatibility
- ‚úÖ Chrome (recommended)
- ‚úÖ Safari
- ‚úÖ Firefox
- ‚úÖ Edge
- ‚úÖ Mobile browsers

### Network Features
- **Auto-reconnect**: Reconnects if WiFi drops
- **Static IP**: Can be configured in router
- **Port forwarding**: Port 80 for remote access
- **Multiple devices**: Each device needs separate setup

---

## üÜò Support & Maintenance

### Regular Maintenance
- **Check connection**: Ensure device appears in router's device list
- **Update networks**: Factory reset if changing WiFi networks
- **Physical check**: Ensure antennas aren't damaged

### Getting Help
1. **Check this manual** for common solutions
2. **Note error messages** exactly as displayed
3. **Document your network setup** (router model, security type)
4. **Try factory reset** before contacting support

### Advanced Users
- **Port 80**: Web interface
- **Port 81**: WebSocket real-time data
- **EEPROM**: WiFi credentials stored permanently
- **OTA Updates**: Future firmware updates via web interface

---

